mistral.reason: SonicWall was never a subsidiary of Dell. It was originally a private company, then acquired by Dell in 2012, but has now been spun out as an independent company owned by Francisco Partners and Elliott Management.

gemma2.reason: Multiple sources state that Dell acquired SonicWall, not the other way around.

llama3.1.reason: The claim is wrong because SonicWall was actually spun out of Dell Technologies as an independent company, with private equity firm Francisco Partners and hedge fund Elliott Management completing the acquisition.

qwen2.5.reason: SonicWall has officially spun out of Dell Technologies as an independent company, with private equity firm Francisco Partners and hedge fund Elliott Management completing the acquisition of the technology giant's software arm. This means that SonicWall is no longer a subsidiary of Dell but has become privately owned by Francisco Partners and Elliot Management.
